28:11.231 --> 28:12.982
I feel infinite.

28:14.109 --> 28:17.195
♪ And nothing ♪

28:17.279 --> 28:19.781
♪ Will drive them away ♪

28:21.909 --> 28:25.870
♪ We can be heroes ♪

28:25.954 --> 28:28.456
♪ Just for one day ♪ ♪

28:29.708 --> 28:31.042
Dear friend...

28:32.669 --> 28:34.379
I'm sorry I haven't written for a while...

28:34.463 --> 28:37.048
but I've been trying
hard not to be a loser.

28:38.550 --> 28:41.094
For example, I'm trying to participate...

28:41.178 --> 28:43.596
by listening to Sam's collection
of big rock ballads...

28:43.680 --> 28:45.181
and thinking about love.

28:46.850 --> 28:49.435
Sam says they're kitschy and brilliant.

28:49.520 --> 28:50.978
I completely agree.

28:54.858 --> 28:59.070
I'm also writing essays
and studying extra books outside of class.

28:59.154 --> 29:01.948
As it turns out, Mr. Anderson is a writer.

29:02.032 --> 29:03.950
He even had a play put
up in New York once...

29:04.034 --> 29:06.035
which I think is very impressive.

29:06.120 --> 29:07.787
Great Gatsby?

29:07.871 --> 29:11.082
